    "body": "Just want to add that due to the bad interaction of struct bounds and the `deriving` syntax extension, in the case of `CowVec<T>` you are forced to bound `T: Clone` with a `where` clause:\n\nThis compiles:\n\n``` rust\nuse std::vec::CowVec;\n\n#[deriving(Clone)]\nstruct Foo<'a, T: 'a> where T: Clone {\n    bar: CowVec<'a, T>,\n}\n\nfn main() {}\n```\n\nBut this does not:\n\n``` rust\nuse std::vec::CowVec;\n\n#[deriving(Clone)]\nstruct Foo<'a, T: 'a + Clone> {\n    bar: CowVec<'a, T>,\n}\n\nfn main() {}\n```\n\nSee #19361 and #19358 for more details\n",
